### Editorial- and peer review activity

Currently I'm an editorial board member for <a href="https://www.nature.com/srep/" target="_blank">Scientific Reports</a href> (Psychology). My previous editorial responsibilities include

1) Research topic editor for <a href="https://www.frontiersin.org/research-topics/9288/high-performance-cognition-information-processing-in-complex-skills-expert-performance-and-flow" target="_blank">Frontiers in Psychology</a href>
2) Associate editor for <a href="https://jeps.efpsa.org/" target="_blank">Journal of European Psychology Students</a href>
3) Ad hoc academic editor for <a href="https://journals.sagepub.com/home/sgo" target="_blank">Sage OPEN</a href>


I've written about 50 peer reviews, excluding reviews of revised manuscripts, for

1) Journal of Gambling Studies
2) Frontiers in Psychology
3) International Gambling Studies
4) Legal and Criminological Psychology
5) Cognitive Science
6) International Journal of Human-Computer Studies
7) Neuropsychiatric Disease and Treatment
8) Gerontology
9) IEEE Access
10) Learning and Individual Differences
11) Basic and Applied Social Psychology
12) Nordic Conference on Human-Computer Interaction
13) Workshop on Socio-Technical Aspects in Security and Trust
14) Routledge Books (Applied Psychology)
15) IGI Global
16) Annual Meeting of the Cognitive Science Society
17) SAGE Open
18) Journal of Behavioral Addictions.